-- Saudi Arabian Bounced Checks Decline 50%, Al-Eqtisadiah Says
-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 2012-02-11T08:05:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-11/saudi-arabian-bounced-checks-decline-50-al-eqtisadiah-says.html
Saudi Arabia  reported a 50 percent
decrease in the value of bounced checks at the end of 2011,  al-
Eqtisadiah  reported, citing a report released by the  Saudi
Credit Bureau .  The amount fell to 10 billion riyals ($2.7 billion) as of
Dec. 31, from 5 billion riyals a year earlier, the newspaper
said. The number of bounced checks decreased to 52,000 from
101,000, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in Riyadh at 
 mharoutunian@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
